<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TMaL42">
<l>paḻutilā voḻuka lāṟṟup palacatup pēti mārka</l>
<l>ḷiḻikulat tavarka ḷēlu memmaṭi yārka ḷākil</l>
<l>toḻumiṉīr koṭumiṉ koṇmi ṉeṉṟuniṉ ṉōṭu mokka</l>
<l>vaḻipaṭa varuḷi ṉāypōṉm matiṭṭiru varaṅkat tāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>‘[O you,] the many Brahmins well-versed in the four Vedas from a flowing,</l>
<l>faultless stream [of lineages]!</l>
<l>Even if they are of low castes, if they are Our devotees,</l>
<l>You worship [them], give [them], and take [from them]!’</l>
<l>Thus You seem to have graciously said that [they] should be worshipped same as You,</l>
<l>O You from Śrīraṅgam with golden ramparts!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
